Source: pg-dbms-lock
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/HexaCluster/pg_dbms_lock

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-dbms-lock
Architecture: all
Provides: postgresql-pg-dbms-lock
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-background (>= 2.0), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Oracle DBMS_LOCK compatibility for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 pg_dbms_lock implements Oracle-compatible named and numeric advisory lock
 operations, including allocation, requests with shared or exclusive modes,
 explicit release, timeout handling, and sleep support.
